title: Victoria Bus Station
description:
Victoria bus station is a bus station outside Victoria Mainline Rail Station in Terminus Place, in the City of Westminster district of London the capital of the United Kingdom.

It services only local London bus services managed by Transport for London, and should not be confused with Victoria Coach Station, which is the main London terminus for long distance coach services operated by National Express, http://wikimapia.org/#lang=en&lat=51.492744&lon=-0.149115&z=18&m=b&show=/20822/  or alternatively the newer Victoria Green Line Coach Station, which serves coach operators other than National Express http://wikimapia.org/#lang=en&lat=51.493061&lon=-0.146921&z=18&m=b&show=/580722/

Victoria is London's busiest bus station, with 19 bus routes using the station, with 200 buses per hour passing through in the peak. It formerly had a substantial roof canopy spanning all lanes. This was demolished in April 2003 as part of the station's refurbishment.

title: SkyGarden tower-approved
description:
Developer Fraser Projects has been given the go-ahead for this mixed-use tower in Vauxhall, London.

The 120m Vauxhall Sky Gardens, designed by architects Amin Taha Associates and Carey Jones, will comprise 34 floors with 178 flats plus offices and shops.

Alliance Planning, which acted as consultant on the application, said: “This is a major regeneration proposal, and is the first tall building to win approval following the election of Boris Johnson.

urlhtml: Heathwall Sewage Pumping Station and Combined Sewer Overflow
title: Heathwall Sewage Pumping Station and Combined Sewer Overflow
description:
A Thames Water Utilities Ltd. facility. Heathwall Sewage Pumping Station is on the southern low level outfall sewer that feeds into Crossness Sewage Treatment Works.

In the event of rain or high flows in the low level sewer the Pumping Station will feed a Combined Sewer Overflow outlet on the thames and dump access sewage untreated straight into the Thames.

The Thames Tideway tunnel will intercept this CSO and feed directly into the Thames Tideway Tunnel.
